This is the source for the bitwardenjordan/selfsigned Dockerhub image.

Run this image, e.g.:

`docker run -it bitwardenjordan/selfsigned:latest`

Follow the prompts to generate a root CA and server certificate. At the end, you should see:

```
Verifying the new cert
/usr/src/server.pem: OK
Done!
```

If you do, you can copy `/usr/src/root.pem` (your root CA), `/usr/src/server.pem` (your server cert), and `/usr/src/unencryptedkey.pem` (your unencrypted private key for the server cert) out of the Docker container.

To use these in Bitwarden, concatenate root.pem on top of server.pem, place the files in your bwdata/ssl directory, and reference their locations in config.yml.
